sentences: Eleanor Friede (d. 2008) was an American book editor and literary agent, best known for bringing the novella Jonathan Livingston Seagull to publication.
She married Donald Friede, a World Publishing editor, in 1951.
Friede was working as a marketing director at Macmillan in 1968 when company president Jeremiah Kaplan convinced her to become an editor.
In 1974, Friede received her own imprint at Delacorte Press.
It was published in 1976, with an English version being published in 1977.

Eleanor Friede died July 14, 2008, at the age of 78.
Following Delacorte's purchase by Doubleday in the early 1980s she launched Eleanor Friede Books, a literary agency.
A year later she persuaded Macmillan to buy Jonathan Livingston Seagull, a fable about a seagull who breaks from his flock in search of freedom.
